# Trivy false positive suppressions for complytime-deploy.
#
# This project uses Kustomize with base manifests and overlay patches.
# Trivy scans each YAML file standalone, but overlay patches are partial
# strategic-merge documents — security controls live in the base manifests
# and are merged at build time. All KSV rules below fire on partial patches
# that lack fields already present in the base.
#
# The validate job in ci_validate.yml scans the merged output
# via task sk:render-all -> Trivy on .rendered-manifests/. These
# suppressions remain for the ci_security.yml Trivy workflow which
# still scans raw files.

# Namespace is set by Kustomize overlay (kustomization.yaml sets namespace
# per environment). Base manifests intentionally omit metadata.namespace
# so kustomize can inject it at build time.
KSV-0110

# Images from quay.io/complytime, docker.io/grafana, and docker.io/rustfs
# are the project's own images or well-known FOSS images. These registries
# are trusted for this project.
KSV-0125

# Image tags (:latest, :unstable) are intentional per overlay design.
# Production uses :latest, stage uses :unstable. Digest pinning is
# deliberately not used (see CKV_K8S_43 inline suppressions).
KSV-0013

# --- Kustomize partial-patch false positives ---
# Base deployments set allowPrivilegeEscalation: false, but patches that
# only override env vars or resources don't repeat the field.
KSV-0001

# Base deployments drop ALL capabilities. Patches don't repeat this.
KSV-0003
KSV-0004
KSV-0106

# Resource limits and requests are set in base or the resources.yaml patch.
# Other patches (env, images, probes) don't repeat resource fields.
KSV-0011
KSV-0015
KSV-0016
KSV-0018

# Base deployments set runAsNonRoot: true. Patches don't repeat this.
KSV-0012

# Base deployments set readOnlyRootFilesystem: true. Patches don't repeat this.
KSV-0014

# Base deployments set runAsUser/runAsGroup > 10000. Patches don't repeat this.
KSV-0020
KSV-0021

# Base deployments set seccompProfile to RuntimeDefault. Patches don't repeat this.
KSV-0030
KSV-0104

# Base deployments have full securityContext. Patches don't repeat this.
KSV-0118
